<font color="#FF0000">TO TAO GUO</font><br>
<tt>Mon Jun 23 21:29:47 US/Eastern 1997
</tt><p>
Tao GUO,<br><br>
Thank you for your understanding and sensitivity toward the issues on these pages. Your honesty makes me proud that we really did fight for something, even if we &quot;lost&quot;. That is very important to me. I struggle with my pair of opposites with the Vietnam War constantly at some level in my mind looking for the answer that never really comes to light.<br><br>
I sense that there is no definitive answer. Solice lies in understanding many points of view, and knowing the truth lies somewhere in between.<br><br>
I am very happy for you that you have found freedom in this country. So many take it for granted that we sometimes forget what it means to be without.<br><br>
Welcome, for this is your country too, as it is for countless others. <br><br>
Thank you for sharing your feelings. I apprecite it.<br><br>
Arthur<br><br>

